hallenges of vulnerable fathers such as those in poverty or in prison, they have developed valuable new strategies for cultivating the positive involvement of fathers in the lives of their children.Drawing on the innovative work of Prospère, a Quebec organization that brought together fathers, university researchers, and health and social service practitioners, Fathering details innovative approaches that support positive father involvement. It provides numerous examples of strategies and interventions with fathers, lessons learned from these practices on how to better support vulnerable fathers and families, and in-depth information on ways of designing, implementing, evaluating, and disseminating the results of participatory action research (PAR) – a methodology which put fathers at the heart of the project’s decision-making.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aFather and child. 0aFatherhood. 0aFathers. 0aParenting. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh1 aBall, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrette, Martine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBizot, Dominic, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoutu, Sylvain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Finney, Sandrina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDevault, Annie , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDevault, Annie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoré, Jeanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDubeau, Diane , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDubeau, Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForget, Gilles, econtributor.4ctb4https://